headline: ACV Auctions, eBay, Chewy, Expedia, and Chegg Shares Are Falling, What You Need To Know
summary: A number of stocks fell in the afternoon session after investor fears over artificial intelligence disrupting the software industry sparked a broad sell-off. The anxiety stemmed from the rapid adoption of new 'agentic AI' tools, which some investors believed could dismantle traditional Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) business models.
